711111f-b.title: Manhattan: 11th Street - West Street
711111f-b.text:
(1)
11th Street (formerly Hammond Street), south side, from West to
Washington Streets, showinrg the old shack, 425 West Street,
at the corner. The buildings on the S.W. corner of Washington
Street were Uemiolished two years earlier, and the railroad
viaduct has not yet been built.
Notice the slum children here and there in the picture, especial
the three little ones in the left foreground.
July 30, 1932.
P.  L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, three years earlier. Notice how the corner building,
125 West Street, looked before the upper two floors were
removed.
March 8, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
